"script": "What if you froze your body to wake up in the future? The plan sounds simple: chill yourself until a cure exists, then thaw out good as new. But here's the catch. The water inside your cells freezes into sharp ice crystals. And those crystals slice your cells apart from the inside, like tiny knives. So scientists swap your blood for antifreeze to stop it. Yet nobody has ever truly thawed a frozen human back to life. Right now, the people waiting in those cold tanks aren't really sleeping. They're betting everything that someone, someday, learns to turn ice back into you.",
